 \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999427460379738, \"rank\": 0.0005654461916398016, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"almost every town\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1457}, {\"ngram\": \"the route\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"admirers\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"their devotion\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"garlands\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"photographs\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the open car\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was given unique welcome at hotels in the Sahiwal district, including those on the Arifwala, Pakpattan, Harappa, and Chichawatni bypasses.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arif_Wala_Tehsil\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arifwala\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arif_Wala_Tehsil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arif_Wala_Tehsil\"}, {\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakpattan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.546866222168928e-13, \"text\": \"Pakpattan\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakpattan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakpattan\"}, {\"begin\": 1703, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harappa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harappa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harappa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harappa\"}, {\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chichawatni\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chichawatni\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chichawatni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chichawatni\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"unique welcome\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"hotels\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sahiwal district\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Sargodha, Mohammad Farooq had traveled for hours to take part in the welcome festivities.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sargodha\", \"score\": 0.9983451265708789, \"rank\": 0.0016576165749223263, \"text\": \"Sargodha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sargodha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sargodha\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mohammad Farooq\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"the welcome festivities\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have come to welcome our hero here.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1873, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our hero\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1867}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This joyous occasion has come to Pakistan after forty years.\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.732237034139162e-20, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This joyous occasion\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1894}, {\"ngram\": \"forty years\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With August 14, it has turned into a double delight, he told Reuters.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.548804750331763e-12, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"a double delight\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arshad made his way through the crowd towards his pleased mother, Raziah Parveen, upon arriving in Mian Chunnu, where supporters were dancing joyfully to the rhythm of drums.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999730116546, \"rank\": 2.6957669922016313e-08, \"text\": \"Mian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Uddin_Ahmed_Chunnu\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chunnu\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Uddin_Ahmed_Chunnu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Uddin_Ahmed_Chunnu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Arshad\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"his pleased mother\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"Raziah Parveen\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"supporters\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"the rhythm\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"drums\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then collapsed to her feet.\", \"from\": 2181, \"